	<div class="posts">
	<a name="108553370962304189">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<h3>What's It All About? Objects, Languages, and Meaning</h3><a href="http://channel9.msdn.com/ShowPost.aspx?PostID=8628#8628">Ward Cunningham - Do you get religious about programming languages?</a>.&nbsp; This Channel 9 <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/winme/0405/22606/Cunningham/Languages_Ward.asx">video interview</a> with Ward Cunningham (the third so far) includes some fascinating observations about objects as little language machines.&nbsp; I think this provides something useful about the nature of protocols too.<br /><br />What I want people to notice is at the end where Ward talks about a stock trading application and how they learned about a discrepancy in the use of the same technical term by different communities when they set out to automate some of the procedures.&nbsp; Listen for the observation about finding the appropriate abstraction (such that days are not about hours and minutes). <br>
